TheÂ African UnionÂ (AU) is aÂ continental unionÂ consisting of fifty-five African states.Â Established in 2001, the AU's purpose is to help secure Africa's democracy, human rights, and a sustainable economy, especially by bringing an end to intra-African conflict and creating an effective common market.

