TheÂ Organization of American StatesÂ (OAS) is an international organization, headquartered in Washington, D.C., United States. Its members are the thirty-five independent states of the Americas. Over the course of the 1990s, with the end of theÂ Cold War, the return to democracy in Latin America, and the thrust towardÂ globalization, the OAS made major efforts to reinvent itself to fit the new context. Its stated priorities now include the following:

