Nature, in the broadest sense, is theÂ physicalÂ world orÂ universe. "Nature" can refer to theÂ phenomenaÂ of the physical world, and also to life in general. The study of nature is a large, if not the only, part ofÂ science. Although humans are part of nature, human activity is often understood as a separate category from other natural phenomena.

