Earth is estimated to have formed 4.54Â billion years ago from theÂ solar nebula, along with theÂ SunÂ and otherÂ planets.Â The Moon formed roughly 20Â million years later. Initially molten, the outer layer of the Earth cooled, resulting in the solid crust. Outgassing andÂ volcanicÂ activity produced the primordial atmosphere. CondensingÂ water vapor, most or all of which came fromÂ iceÂ delivered byÂ comets,Â produced the oceansÂ and other water sources.Â The highly energetic chemistry is believed to have produced a self-replicating molecule around 4Â billion years ago.

