Digital currencyÂ (digital money,Â electronic moneyÂ orÂ electronic currency) is anyÂ currency,Â money, or money-like asset that is primarily managed, stored or exchanged on digital computer systems, especially over theÂ internet. Types of digital currencies includeÂ cryptocurrency,Â virtual currencyÂ andÂ central bank digital currency. Digital currency may be recorded on aÂ distributed databaseÂ on the internet, a centralized electronicÂ computer databaseÂ owned by a company or bank, withinÂ digital filesÂ or even on aÂ stored-value card.

