Law

Since 2001, the European Union has implemented theÂ E-Money DirectiveÂ "on the taking up, pursuit and prudential supervision of the business of electronic money institutions" last amended in 2009.

In the United States, electronic money is governed by Article 4A of theÂ Uniform Commercial CodeÂ for wholesale transactions and theÂ Electronic Fund Transfer ActÂ for consumer transactions. Provider's responsibility and consumer's liability are regulated under Regulation E.

Regulation

Virtual currencies pose challenges for central banks, financial regulators, departments or ministries of finance, as well as fiscal authorities and statistical authorities.

